![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1489ed37-65eb-4202-aad5-b9f616cd28dc/13689.jpg?format=original)

After her turn on Dancing With the Stars last year, rugby star and Olympic bronze medalist Ilona Maher is considering a new kind of spotlight.

She recently revealed to BBC Sport that she’s “been approached before by the WWE,” adding that if she joined the company, her ring name would be “Maher-vellous.” Maher said, “I don’t know if I would \[go into wrestling\]. I should think about it, there is great money in it,” noting that she also has her eyes on the “acting space.”

Maher's background as a USA Rugby Olympian gives her a unique advantage in any physical role. Known for her powerful tackles and commanding presence on the field, her athletic skillset translates well to the physical demands of pro wrestling.

Beyond her athletic prowess, Maher has also cultivated a large social media following, particularly on TikTok, where her humorous and relatable content has earned her a reputation for charisma and stage presence.